Of the 115 variants from two genomic loci identified in the meta-analysis, 73 were also significantly associated with docility scores (P < 0.05 in the validation GWAS) in at least one of the replication cohorts. This number of validated variants is significantly larger than expected by chance (29.6 in 50,000 replicates, P < 2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
