There are some limitations to our findings. One potential caveat could be the effect of residual population stratification on these results which would increase the number of false positives. In order to control for population stratification, models for each cohort included all available covariates: age, contemporary group (year, stud, sex), the GRM fitted as a random effect, as well as genomic control (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
